The Nigeria Football Fed­eration (NFF) has direct­ed Football Associations in the 36 States and the Federal Capital Territo­ry (FCT) to take charge of registration of teams that will compete in this year’s AITEO Federation Cup competition. In a circular on Wednesday, the Feder­ation directed that the registration of teams for this year’s edition of the country’s most glamor­ous football champion­ship should commence on Sunday, May 1, 2022 and last for 13 days. Submission of copies of completed players’ li­censes to the NFF must be done latest Saturday, May 14, while the competition in the States, to select two representatives for the na­tional competition, will hold between May 15 and June 15. The NFF’s Competi­tions Department expects to have the names of each State’s two flagbearers for the national competition by June 15. Bayelsa United are the defending champi­ons